DITA MAP document typeassociation rulesA file is considered to be a DITA map document when either of the following occurs:
root element name is one of the following: map, bookmap;
public id of the document is -//OASIS//DTD DITA Map or -//OASIS//DTD DITA BookMap;
the root element of the file has an attribute named class which contains the value map/map and a DITAArchVersion attribute from the http://dita.oasis-open.org/architecture/2005/ namespace. This enhanced case of matching is only applied when the Enable DTD processing option from the Document Type Detection option pageDocument Type Detection option page is enabled.
